Git merge is a command in Git (a version control system) that combines changes from one branch into another branch.

In simple words:
👉 It joins two branches together.

🔹 Why Do We Use Git Merge?

When multiple developers work on different features using separate branches, we use git merge to combine those changes into the main branch (like main or master).
